      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HES RUNAWAY BAY (6) broke last start and finished 9 metres from the winner in sixth over 2180m at Terang in an inauspicious start to his career. Won't find this any harder so he can return to form. DALAHASTEN (2) was in the money at Bendigo two runs ago before having his colours lowered at his latest appearance over 1650m at Bendigo, beaten 35 metres. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. This is a nice drop in grade so he is in the right race to return to form. REDBLUENPURPLE (7) was unplaced two starts ago then things went wrong last start when he broke and finished 13 metres away in seventh over 2180m at Terang. Will need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position. Meets a similar line up so if he behaves a big run is likely. I AM SKYE CHIOLA (5) is the best of the rest after finishing runner-up over 2180m at Terang last time out.",
